metadata.name: Indra #1
metadata.description:
Indra goes to war!

"Indra" is the most important god in Indo-Iranian Vedism. Indra is the god of "light", "rain", "ripper of clouds", "splitter of mountains" and the god of "thunder", who fights against "Vortrag", god of "darkness" and "famin", and defeats him.
